    "apply_url": "https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/bevel/a71e6b6d-8153-459e-8fca-4c4843f73fac/application",
    "company": "Bevel",
    "compensation": "",
    "content_hash": "41edb85aa24f233a",
    "department": "Design",
    "description": "ABOUT BEVEL\n\nBevel is the #1 AI Health Companion with over 1 million downloads globally. We help people make smarter decisions about their health every day by bringing together data across sleep, recovery, activity, nutrition, and more, and turning it into real-time, personalized guidance. Whether you're training for something big or just trying to feel better, Bevel helps you move with clarity and confidence.\n\nWe are a small, fast-moving team based in NYC, passionate about building beautiful and functional products. We are constantly looking for creative ways to push the capabilities of iOS/watchOS to create an app that is more intelligent, fun, and integrated into our users’ lives.\n\nBevel launched in early 2024, and we’ve been lucky to see incredible growth and support from our users. We’re looking to bring on additional designers to help us build an ambitious roadmap https://feedback.bevel.health/. You’ll get an opportunity to shape the future of Bevel and have full ownership and creative freedom to create your life’s work.\n\n\nRESPONSIBILITIES\n\n - Lead end-to-end design projects\n\n - Create flows, prototypes, and high-fidelity visuals for features\n\n - Scope and document requirements of features from a design standpoint\n\n - Work closely with our engineers to deliver a product end-to-end\n\n - Develop a deep understanding of the latest information and technology in the wearable/health space\n\n\nREQUIREMENTS\n\n - At least 2 years of experience\n\n - A portfolio of excellent product designs\n\n - Ability to take high-level concepts and turn them into well-scope requirements\n\n - Ability to write effective design documentation\n\n - Ability to work independently and drive projects end-to-end\n\n - Experience using Figma and building flows, prototypes, and high-fidelity visuals\n\n - Obsessive about craft and excited about improving the health \u0026 fitness of others\n\n - Multiple years of wearing an Apple Watch\n\n\nNICE TO HAVE\n\n - Experience with mobile apps\n\n - Up-to-date on the best products in the health/fitness space\n\n - Background in computer science\n\n\nBENEFITS\n\n - Exciting work environment\n\n - Competitive salary \u0026 equity\n\n - Health, dental, and vision insurance\n\n - Commuter benefits\n\n - Paid lunch and dinner\n\n - Work-life harmony\n\n - Pet-friendly office in Chelsea\n\n - Unlimited PTO\n\n - 401(k) plan\n\n - Visa sponsorship if applicable\n\nBevel celebrates and embraces diversity and is committed to building a team that represents a variety of experiences, backgrounds, and skills. We do not discriminate based on race, color, religion, marital status, age, gender identity, gender expression, sexual orientation, non-disqualifying physical or mental disability, national origin, veteran status, or other applicable legally protected characteristics.",
